---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Pay Off Debt or Keep Cash Calculator
description: Compare paying down debt with keeping cash in savings, including interest avoided, after-tax savings interest, payoff timing, liquidity, and an optional investment scenario.
navKey: tools
tags: tools
scripts:
  - /assets/tools/debt-or-cash.js
---

<div class="calculator-page">
    <section class="page-hero page-hero-compact">
        <p class="eyebrow">Debt versus liquidity</p>

        <h1>Pay Off Debt or Keep Cash Calculator</h1>

        <p class="hero-copy">
            Compare the guaranteed benefit of reducing debt with the
            after-tax return and liquidity of keeping money in savings.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section
        class="calculator-card"
        data-debt-or-cash-calculator
        aria-label="Pay off debt or keep cash calculator"
    >
        <div class="calculator-input-grid">
            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="debtBalance">
                    Current debt balance
                </label>

                <input
                    id="debtBalance"
                    type="number"
                    min="0.01"
                    step="any"
                    value="200000"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="debtApr">
                    Debt interest rate (APR)
                </label>

                <div class="calculator-input-suffix">
                    <input
                        id="debtApr"
                        type="number"
                        min="0"
                        max="100"
                        step="0.001"
                        value="6.875"
                        inputmode="decimal"
                    >

                    <span aria-hidden="true">%</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="remainingTermYears">
                    Remaining term in years
                </label>

                <input
                    id="remainingTermYears"
                    type="number"
                    min="0.01"
                    max="100"
                    step="any"
                    value="25"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >

                <small>
                    Used when monthly payment is blank.
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="monthlyDebtPayment">
                    Current monthly payment
                </label>

                <input
                    id="monthlyDebtPayment"
                    type="number"
                    min="0.01"
                    step="any"
                    placeholder="Optional"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >

                <small>
                    Enter principal and interest only for a mortgage.
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="liquidCash">
                    Liquid cash available
                </label>

                <input
                    id="liquidCash"
                    type="number"
                    min="0"
                    step="any"
                    value="50000"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="emergencyReserve">
                    Emergency fund to keep
                </label>

                <input
                    id="emergencyReserve"
                    type="number"
                    min="0"
                    step="any"
                    value="20000"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="savingsApy">
                    Savings account APY
                </label>

                <div class="calculator-input-suffix">
                    <input
                        id="savingsApy"
                        type="number"
                        min="0"
                        max="100"
                        step="0.001"
                        value="4.6"
                        inputmode="decimal"
                    >

                    <span aria-hidden="true">%</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="federalTaxRate">
                    Federal marginal tax rate
                </label>

                <div class="calculator-input-suffix">
                    <input
                        id="federalTaxRate"
                        type="number"
                        min="0"
                        max="100"
                        step="0.1"
                        value="22"
                        inputmode="decimal"
                    >

                    <span aria-hidden="true">%</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="stateTaxRate">
                    State marginal tax rate
                </label>

                <div class="calculator-input-suffix">
                    <input
                        id="stateTaxRate"
                        type="number"
                        min="0"
                        max="100"
                        step="0.1"
                        value="0"
                        inputmode="decimal"
                    >

                    <span aria-hidden="true">%</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="investmentReturn">
                    Expected investment return
                </label>

                <div class="calculator-input-suffix">
                    <input
                        id="investmentReturn"
                        type="number"
                        min="-99.99"
                        max="100"
                        step="0.01"
                        placeholder="Optional"
                        inputmode="decimal"
                    >

                    <span aria-hidden="true">%</span>
                </div>

                <small>
                    Adds a separate, uncertain market comparison.
                </small>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p
            class="calculator-error"
            id="debtOrCashError"
            role="alert"
        ></p>

        <div class="article-callout">
            <p
                id="liquidityNotice"
                aria-live="polite"
            >
                Results will appear after valid values are entered.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="calculator-results"
            aria-live="polite"
        >
            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Cash applied to debt
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="cashApplied"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small>
                    Cash above the protected reserve, capped at the debt
                balance
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Guaranteed interest avoided
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="interestAvoided"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="interestAvoidedDescription">
                    Estimated over the remaining payoff period
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    After-tax savings interest
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="savingsInterest"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="savingsInterestDescription">
                    Estimated interest earned by keeping the compared cash
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Break-even savings APY
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="breakEvenApy"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="afterTaxSavingsYield">
                    Gross APY needed for the after-tax yield to match the
                    debt cost
                </small>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="calculator-explanation">
            <h2>Payoff timing and monthly cash flow</h2>

            <p>
                The calculator assumes the same scheduled monthly debt
                payment continues after a lump-sum payment. Once the debt
                is gone, that payment becomes available for saving,
                investing, or other spending.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="calculator-results"
            aria-live="polite"
        >
            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    New payoff estimate
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="newPayoffDate"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="currentPayoffDescription">
                    Current payoff estimate will appear here
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Time saved
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="timeSaved"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small>
                    Estimated reduction in the remaining payoff period
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Monthly cash-flow improvement
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="monthlyCashFlow"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small>
                    Scheduled payment available after the debt is paid
                </small>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="calculator-explanation">
            <h2>Which strategy is ahead over time?</h2>

            <p>
                These results compare estimated net worth under two
                strategies. One keeps the cash in savings and continues
                the current debt payment. The other uses cash above the
                emergency reserve to reduce debt and redirects the monthly
                payment to savings after payoff.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="calculator-results"
            aria-live="polite"
        >
            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Difference after 1 year
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="differenceOneYear"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="differenceOneYearDescription">
                    Strategy comparison
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Difference after 5 years
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="differenceFiveYears"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="differenceFiveYearsDescription">
                    Strategy comparison
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Difference after 10 years
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="differenceTenYears"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small id="differenceTenYearsDescription">
                    Strategy comparison
                </small>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section
            id="investmentComparison"
            hidden
        >
            <div class="calculator-explanation">
                <h2>Optional investment comparison</h2>

                <p>
                    This separate scenario assumes cash above the emergency
                    reserve is invested instead of held in savings. Market
                    returns are uncertain and may be negative, especially
                    over shorter periods. Taxes on investment gains are not
                    included.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div
                class="calculator-results"
                aria-live="polite"
            >
                <div class="calculator-result">
                    <span class="calculator-result-label">
                        Keep cash invested
                    </span>

                    <strong
                        class="calculator-result-value"
                        id="keepInvestedNetWorth"
                    >
                        —
                    </strong>

                    <small>
                        Estimated net worth after 10 years
                    </small>
                </div>

                <div class="calculator-result">
                    <span class="calculator-result-label">
                        Pay debt first
                    </span>

                    <strong
                        class="calculator-result-value"
                        id="payDebtInvestedNetWorth"
                    >
                        —
                    </strong>

                    <small>
                        Estimated net worth after 10 years
                    </small>
                </div>

                <div class="calculator-result">
                    <span class="calculator-result-label">
                        Market scenario difference
                    </span>

                    <strong
                        class="calculator-result-value"
                        id="investmentDifference"
                    >
                        —
                    </strong>

                    <small id="investmentDifferenceDescription">
                        Strategy comparison using the assumed return
                    </small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="calculator-explanation">
            <h2>How this calculator works</h2>

            <p>
                Paying debt produces a return equal to the interest that
                no longer accrues. That benefit is treated as guaranteed
                when the debt rate and repayment terms are fixed.
            </p>

            <p>
                Savings interest is reduced using the combined federal and
                state marginal tax rates entered. This is a simplified
                estimate. It does not model deductions, exemptions, tax
                brackets, or account-specific tax treatment.
            </p>

            <div class="formula-grid">
                <div class="formula-card">
                    <span>Cash available for debt</span>

                    <code>
                        Liquid cash - protected emergency reserve
                    </code>
                </div>

                <div class="formula-card">
                    <span>Net-worth comparison</span>

                    <code>
                        Savings and investments - remaining debt
                    </code>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>
                The break-even APY is the gross savings yield needed for
                its estimated after-tax monthly return to match the
                monthly cost of the debt. APR and APY are not identical,
                so the break-even APY may be higher than the stated debt
                APR even before taxes.
            </p>

            <p>
                Liquidity is not a rounding error. Money sent to a lender
                is no longer sitting in the account waiting for the water
                heater to develop opinions. The calculator protects the
                emergency reserve entered, but it cannot determine whether
                that reserve is adequate for a particular household.
            </p>

            <p>
                When a monthly payment is entered, the calculator assumes
                that fixed amount continues until payoff and ignores the
                remaining-term input. For credit cards, enter the amount
                actually expected to be paid each month rather than a
                variable minimum-payment formula.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    {% include "components/debt-or-cash-related-guide.njk" %}

    <p class="tool-disclaimer">
        For educational purposes only. Results are estimates and assume
        monthly debt interest, a constant savings yield, fixed tax rates,
        and a constant monthly payment. Mortgage-interest deductions,
        escrow, prepayment penalties, promotional balance-transfer terms,
        transfer fees, investment taxes, and changing rates are not
        included. Paying debt can reduce liquidity, and assumed investment
        returns are not guaranteed.
    </p>
</div>
